# Run and Fix — No Ask-to-Run

- **Run scripts and commands yourself**: Use the terminal to run `npm run types`, `npm run type-check`, `npm run build`, `npm test`, `npm run deploy`, etc. Do not tell the user to run them.
- **Run tests after changes**: Execute the test suite (e.g. `npm test`) and fix failures before concluding.
- **Fix errors**: If a command, test, or linter fails, fix the cause and re-run until it passes. Do not leave a list of "run this to fix" unless the fix requires user-only input or secrets.
- **Windows fallback**: If `npm`/`npx` are not in PATH in the current shell, use `cmd /c "cd /d C:\WorkSpaces\voicetowebsite-copyright-mrjwswain && <command>"` to run from the project root.
- **Only ask the user to run** when the action requires interactive auth, 2FA, or a secret not available to the agent.
